# The repo root is a Docker build context for services whose Dockerfile copies a sibling module (for
# a `replace` directive or the shared eventbus lib) plus their own module: proof-validator (work03),
# the mpesa-adapter CORE (work04), and — work15 — paylink-service, notification-service,
# payment-orchestrator, chain-event-mirror, and the eventbus-go/eventbus-python libs. Exclude only
# what none of those images build from, so the context stays small.

# Clients / docs the repo-root images do not build from.
# Keep adapters/mpesa (the Go core builds from the repo root); exclude any other adapters and the
# Node rail service (it builds from its own context, not the repo root).
adapters/*
!adapters/mpesa/
adapters/mpesa/daraja-service/
apps/
sdks/
docs/
monitoring/
infra/
.claude/
.github/

# VCS, IDE, design files.
.git/
*.pen

# Chain runtime data + node key (not needed to build; never ship secrets).
paylink-chain/data/
**/*.key

# Language caches / build artifacts / coverage.
**/node_modules/
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.coverage
**/coverage.out
**/htmlcov/
**/bin/
